'''PowerReviews''' develops and markets [[engagement marketing|consumer engagement]] technology for brands and retailers. The company has offices in Chicago & London.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/blog/techflash/2014/06/powerreviews-bazaarvoice-viewpoints.html|title=PowerReviews gets acquired after antitrust suit forces Texas firm to sell it|author=Patrick Hoge|date=4 June 2014|website= |publisher=San Francisco Business Times}}</ref>

PowerReviews, founded in 2005,  provides technology and tools for retailers and e-commerce companies to host product reviews on their websites.<ref>{{ cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/blog/techflash/2014/06/powerreviews-bazaarvoice-viewpoints.html|author=Michael Arrington|title=Product Reviews: Everyone Wants a Piece of The Market, But PowerReviews May Get It. |publisher=TechCrunch.}}</ref> It also works with brands and manufacturers to syndicate reviews from their sites to e-commerce sites where their products are being sold.<ref>{{ cite web| url=https://techcrunch.com/2011/07/26/powerreviews/|publisher=TechCrunch|title=PowerReviews Spreads Consumer Reviews Between E-Commerce Sites}}</ref> 

The firm provides technology and tools for retailers and [[e-commerce]] companies to host product reviews on their websites.<ref name="TC1">{{cite web |url= https://techcrunch.com/2007/04/09/product-reviews-everyone-wants-a-piece-of-the-market-but-powerreviews-may-get-it/|title=Product Reviews: Everyone Wants a Piece of The Market, But PowerReviews May Get It |author=Michael Arrington|date=9 April 2007|website= |publisher=TechCrunch}}</ref>
It also works with brands and manufacturers to syndicate reviews from their sites to e-commerce sites where their products are being sold.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://techcrunch.com/2011/07/26/powerreviews/|title=PowerReviews Spreads Consumer Reviews Between E-Commerce Sites|author=Erick Schonfeld|date=26 July 2011|website= |publisher=TechCrunch}}</ref>

PowerReviews moderates more than 30,000,000 reviews a year for over 1,000 clients and gathers product reviews and ratings online from an audience of more than 250,000 consumers, which it publishes on the sites of more than 2,500 e-tailers with a total of 500 million customers. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/20150502/issue01/305029993/how-matt-moog-got-gut-punched-by-google-and-still-won|publisher=Crains|author=john pletz|title=How Matt Moog got gut-punched by Google and still won|date=2015-05-02}}</ref>
 
As of 2016, PowerReviews reaches more than 700 million in-market shoppers and spans more than 1000 global brands and 5000 websites.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://retailsdigitalsummit.nrf.com/company/powerreviews |title=PowerReviews Shop.org|publisher=Shop.org}}</ref>

==Acquisition by viewpoints==

In 2012, PowerReviews was acquired by competitor [[Bazaarvoice]] for $168 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2012/05/24/bazaarvoice-acquires-powerreviews/|title=Bazaarvoice To Acquire PowerReviews for $151M|author=Anthony Ha|date=24 May 2012|website= |publisher=TechCrunch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.zdnet.com/blog/btl/bazaarvoice-acquires-rival-powerreviews-adds-smbs-to-social-crm-portfolio/78137| title=Bazaarvoice acquires rival PowerReviews; adds SMBs to social CRM portfolio|author=Andrew Nusca|date=25 May 2012|website= |publisher=ZDNet}}</ref> The acquisition was opposed by the [[United States Department of Justice]] for [[antitrust]] concerns,   focused on the ratings and review industry's relatively small marketplace and the potential importance to adjacent industries.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fair|first1=Rebecca Kirk|title=Sizing Up the Competition: Antitrust Enforcement and the Bazaarvoice Ruling|url=http://www.natlawreview.com/article/sizing-competition-antitrust-enforcement-and-bazaarvoice-ruling|accessdate=17 September 2014|work=The National Law Review|publisher=Analysis Group|date=29 August 2014}}</ref>    In 2014, consumer reviews company Viewpoints purchased PowerReviews from Bazaarvoice. The two companies combined under the PowerReviews name.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.internetretailer.com/2014/06/05/consumer-reviews-platform-powerreviews-back | title=Consumer reviews platform PowerReviews is back|author=Allison Enright|date=5 June 2014|website= |publisher=Internet Retailer}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://techcrunch.com/2014/06/04/bazaarvoice-sells-powerreviews/?| title=After Antitrust Suit, Bazaarvoice Sells PowerReviews To Review Site Viewpoints for $30M|author=Anthony Ha|date=4 June 2014|website= |publisher=TechCrunch}}</ref>

